   {:e #blake3 "42f5c0ed17ff86b19344fb4c76420166079db58df3798079c22eba9b95a704b9" :a :task/description :v "BACKGROUND: The filesystem watcher is the simplest and most universal watcher type. Every project has files. Every meaningful change produces a file modification. This is the minimum viable active observer.. APPROACH: (1) Use notify crate (cross-platform inotify/fsevents/kqueue). (2) Watch paths from :policy/watcher datoms where watcher-type = :watcher.type/filesystem. (3) On file change: invoke the referenced extractor to classify the change. (4) Default classification (no extractor): :component/modified datom with file path and timestamp. (5) With Rust extractor: parse mod.rs changes, detect new/removed modules, assert :component/* datoms. (6) Debounce per file (not global): saves to A and B within window produce 2 datoms (one per file). (7) Ignore patterns: .braid/, target/, .git/ (configurable via :policy/watcher-ignore).. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Touch a watched file -> datom appears in store within debounce_ms. (B) Ignore pattern works: touch .braid/foo -> no datom. (C) 2 files modified simultaneously -> 2 separate datoms. (D) Rapid saves to same file -> exactly 1 datom per debounce window. (E) Watcher stop/restart preserves no duplicate datoms (idempotent). DEPENDS-ON: OBSERVER-1 (t-54ea139b). FILE: crates/braid/src/daemon/fs_watcher.rs (new)" :op :assert}
